lead_paragraph: Breanna Stewart had 15 points, 12 rebounds and nine blocks to help No. 1 UConn extended its winning streak to 55 games, the third-longest in NCAA Division I women's basketball history, with a 90-37 victory over SMU on Saturday.

headline.print_headline: No. 1 UConn Beats SMU 90-37, Runs Winning Streak to 55
